 it was soon decided, could not really be Hungarian, and acts of Parliament soon barred them from taking major roles in cinema production. This book tells the troubled story of that period in Hungarian cinematic history, taking it up through World War II.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aJews in motion pictures. 0aMotion picture industryzHungaryxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszHungaryxHistory. 0aNational characteristics, Hungarian. 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Austria & Hungary.2bisacsh  acinema, Hungary, anti-Semitism, popular film, genre.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048530243zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048530243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048530243/original  a978-3-11-060644-7  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK